  "created": "2026-03-16",
  "description": "Topology 1: the Rössler attractor, single-lobed orbit. More predictable than Lorenz — the Rössler spirals outward from a fixed center before snapping back, producing a quasi-periodic signature closer to a bass oscillator than Lorenz's dual-wing butterfly. chaosIndex 0.12, leash 0.88. Damping high. The result is tonal bass-range chaos: pitched, grounded, with just enough attractor irregularity in the overtones to sound alive. The system that chooses the simplest loop.",
